The paper investigates the downlink performance of massive MIMO systems with one-bit ADC/DACs, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers linear minimum mean-squared-error (LMMSE) channel estimation and matched-filter (MF) precoding, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents numerical results to verify the analysis, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
